betterquesting:10.desc:8: Ok, so you made it to the surface.  Cool!  Your life just got harder!  The air on this planet has been ravaged by a series of natural disasters and is unbreathable.  You need to get inside ASAP!  Use the tools that you brought along with you to secure yourself the best you can!  You can harvest some §0§8Dead Logs§r from the dead trees that dot the landscape.  While you are out searching for §7§8Dead Logs§r, be sure to harvest a few pieces of §7Cobble§r.

By now the air in your space suit should be getting pretty low.  Get your Oxygen system online before you run out of air.  Use the §9Coal Generator§r, the §9Oxygen Vent§r, and the Two §9CO2 Scrubbers§r to set up your oxygen system.  The CO2 scrubbers should be installed on either side of the Oxygen Vent.  Give the Oxygen Vent a §credstone§r signal to start it.

Now that you have a breathable place to live and work, its time to get some food!  You should have everything you need to start a small garden.  As a reminder, cooked potatoes not only taste better, but restore more hunger.  Make a §9furnace§r, grow some food, and you'll feel much better about yourself!

Trees are critical to your continued survival.  Not only can they provide you with crafting materials, but they can be burned to produce fuel for the generator that is keeping you alive.  Trees can be grown inside or outside (remember your space suit if you go outside!). You can use the charge pad and the provided oxygen tanks to provide enough oxygen to go outside and work.  Put that Axe to Work!

If you haven't done so already, you should really get yourself a sword.  As you have seen, the denizens of this planet are nothing to be triffled with!  For now, you will have to make do with a stone or wooden weapon to defend youself.  Not all is lost though, your mind is already spinning with ways to not only survive but to thrive in this landscape.  Make a sword, go protect your new basecamp against those who would take it from you!
No Description
You need to power you calculator, use a Hand Crank Generator connected ot a Power Cube for now.

Now that you have your calculator, you can craft so many more things with just the materials that you have available to you. Check the items that can be made with your calculator and see what you can come up with!

You are feeling much better about your lot in life, soon you will be ready to progress on your own, but before you do that, its probably a good idea to handle one final piece of business.  Producing power is going to be key to your continued survival.  You are probably getting tired of putting coal into that generator.  You notice that there is a constant wind blowing, I bet some sort of windmill would be just the thing!

Ok, so now that you have a Windmill, you'll need a way to get power from it!  Some Low Voltage Connectors are going to be required to move the power from your windmill to your coal generator.  Thankfully you shouldn't have any issues creating these!

I bet you are getting tired of only using flint tools.  As you have been processing items with your calculator, you think you have seen the glint of shiny ores in the cobblestone.  Since Cobblestone is too hard to process, you wonder if breaking it down into §8Gravel§r and then using a piece of §cReinforced Flint§r in a §9Chemist's Table§r would yield any results.

Your excitement and relief is building as you find that you can harvest metals from the ground around you!  I bet you want to go a little crazy and gather all the materials that you can, right?  Go forth and grind them out!  You may need to look at the specific materials and combination of items inside the calculator and Chemist's Table.  If your calculator is getting low on power, you can recharge it in the Power Cube.  Just connect it to power and put the calculator inside!

In all of your ore processing you have probably wondered about how to produce some of the other key materials that are required to produce even more of the key crafting resources.  The scientfic calculator should allow you to take care of these as well.  Its going to take some work, but take the time to craft one.  Your patience will be rewarded by the expansion of automation abilities.
Grass used to contain seeds and you are certain you remember in science class that seeds are extremely hardy..perhaps there are some left you can gather and start the process of creating new life.

The lack of breathable air has made it so normal torches will not work.  It's time to find something else.. you notice some blue glints in the leaves of these dead trees, perhaps there is more than meets the eye?

You have already learned that the applicaton of bonemeal to the ground causes long dormant grasses and flowers to spring forth.  By applying some of that know-how maybe you can coax some magic out of that same ground?  First you will need some special fertilizer!
No Description

By applying the floral fertilizer to the ground, you are rewarded with a few mystical flowers!  There seem to be a lot of different colors!  Don't get amazed by their beauty!  Something tells you that white flowers have a little extra magic in them, try to gather a few.

betterquesting:10.name:8: We need a Book for this stuff!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: During your earlier bonemealing efforts, you probably collected a few different seeds.  Rice can be used for all sorts of things, including paper.  Use paper and some other materials to fashion a book.  From there you can easily craft a special book that will help you make further progress.
You start leafing through the pages of the Lexica Botania, and man is it confusing!  Probably a good place to start is at the very beginning and craft yourself a petal apothecary.

To advance further along the lines of Botania.  You are going to craft some magic infused materials.  The Pure Daisy will draw what little magical energy is in the air out and infuse nearby wood and stone.  Aren't you glad you gathered those white flowers?
To capture the mana stored in the flowers, you must move the mana from them to another place.  The Mana Spreader will handle this task for you.

Now that you can make Mana andtransport it, you need a place to store it.  By making a mana pool, you can store mana for future use.  Pretty Cool, right?  Make a mana pool and start collecting mana, man.

betterquesting:10.name:8: Making Mana while the Sun Shines!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Now that you understand the basics of making flowers, there are some special flowers that can not only make use of the mana in the air, but also produce it!

betterquesting:10.name:8: I want to throw stuff in!
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Now that you have a bit of a stockpile of mana, you can really start to progress.  There are some items that you can throw into the pool to change them.

Throwing stuff into the mana pool is pretty cool, but it gets old kind of quickly, and you can't afford to waste all your other resources by changing them.  An Altar will allow to you to truly progress further, not only in Botania, but in other areas as well.  Be sure to use a Mana Spreader to move mana from your mana pool into the altar
One final item is required so you can become self sufficient.  Having a portable way of storing mana will be helpful for sure.  A mana tablet will allow you to store extra mana in a portable form.
After crashing back to what is supposed to be Earth, you find the world is not as you left it.

This wasteland hides treasures that you haven't even discovered yet!  You have felt the hairs stand up on the back of your neck from something unexplained.  Perhaps some of the ancient science and magic that caused this planet's ruin can be applied to your survival efforts!
